  "prompt": "I'm a rookie. How should I start preparing for getting selected in GSoC 17?",
  "response": "Preparing for Google Summer of Code (GSoC) is an exciting opportunity and requires careful planning. Here are some steps to help you get ready for GSoC 2017:\n\n1. **Understand GSoC**: Familiarize yourself with the program's objectives, timelines, and structure. Read the official GSoC website and the guidelines for both students and mentors.\n\n2. **Choose Your Organization Wisely**:\n   - Browse through the list of participating organizations for 2017 on the GSoC website.\n   - Look for organizations that align with your interests and skills.\n   - Research these organizations to understand their projects, community, and technologies they use.\n\n3. **Get Involved**:\n   - Join the mailing lists, forums, or chat channels (like IRC or Slack) of the organizations you're interested in.\n   - Introduce yourself and express interest in their projects.\n   - Participate in discussions, ask questions, and seek guidance from mentors and community members.\n\n4. **Contribute to the Codebase**:\n   - Start by looking for issues labeled as \"beginner-friendly\" or \"good first issue\" in the organization's repositories on platforms like GitHub.\n   - Follow the contribution guidelines provided by the organization.\n   - Make contributions to the code, docs, or related tasks, and be consistent with your involvement.\n\n5. **Build Relationships**:\n   - Establish rapport with potential mentors by staying active in the community.\n   - Seek feedback on your contributions and ask for advice.\n   - If possible, ask for a mentoring session to get insights on working with the organization.\n\n6. **Identify Project Ideas**:\n   - Check the project ideas list provided by the organization or propose your own ideas.\n   - Discuss your ideas with mentors, get feedback, and refine them further.\n\n7. **Prepare Your Proposal**:\n   - Start writing your proposal early, focusing on clear objectives, a timeline, and expected outcomes.\n   - Showcase your relevant experience, previous contributions, and how you can solve the proposed problem.\n   - Follow the guidelines for writing a proposal provided by GSoC and the organization.\n\n8. **Enhance Skills**:\n   - Identify and improve any technical skills that are relevant to the project you want to work on. This could include programming languages, tools, or frameworks.\n   - Build smaller projects independently or collaborate with others to strengthen your skills.\n\n9. **Time Management**: \n   - Since you'll be juggling multiple tasks, practice managing your time effectively.\n   - Be sure to set aside time for GSoC-related work alongside your other commitments.\n\n10. **Submit Early**: \n    - Submit your proposal before the deadline and ensure you follow all submission instructions.\n    - After submission, continue to engage with the community and mentors to show your enthusiasm.\n\nRemember, GSoC is not just about coding; it\u2019s also about collaboration and communication. Good luck with your preparation!",
